problem_statement:
Java parser idempotency issue when using generics, annotations and arrays
## What version of OpenRewrite are you using?

Current main = a344e18ff346684b0ad9d18cedc57868c1ca0ab6

## What is the smallest, simplest way to reproduce the problem?
```java
    @Test
    void arraysWithAnnotations() {
        rewriteRun(
          java(
            """
            import java.lang.annotation.ElementType;
            import java.lang.annotation.Target;

            class A {
               @Target({ ElementType.TYPE_USE, ElementType.TYPE_PARAMETER })
               private static @interface C {
               }

               Comparable<@C Object @C []> specialArray; 
            }
            """
          )
        );
    }
```
fails with:
```
[When parsing and printing the source code back to text without modifications, the printed source didn't match the original source code. This means there is a bug in the parser implementation itself. Please open an issue to report this, providing a sample of the code that generated this error for "A.java":
```

```diff
-   Comparable<@C Object @C []> specialArray;
+   Comparable<Objectect @C []> specialArray;
```

## Context

OSS repro: https://github.com/classgraph/classgraph/blob/6f9012f2a193ebfefe4a4384e7642820e7aab0f5/src/test/java/io/github/classgraph/issues/issue402/TypeAnnotationTest.java#L65

