problem_statement:
PropertyPlaceholderHelper doesn't handle properties without separation
## What version of OpenRewrite are you using?
I am using

- rewrite-core v8.50.2

## How are you running OpenRewrite?
I am writing a Java recipe.

## What is the smallest, simplest way to reproduce the problem?
Remove the space in the existing single PropertyPlaceholderHelperTest test case
```java
class PropertyPlaceholderHelperTest {
	@Test
	void noSpace() {
		var helper = new PropertyPlaceholderHelper("%%{", "}", null);
		var s = helper.replacePlaceholders("%%{k1}%%{k2}", k -> switch (k) {
			case "k1" -> "hi";
			case "k2" -> "jon";
			default -> throw new UnsupportedOperationException();
		});
		assertThat(s).isEqualTo("hijon");
	}
}
```

## What did you expect to see?
`"hijon"`

## What did you see instead?
`"hi%%{k2}"`

## Are you interested in [contributing a fix to OpenRewrite](https://github.com/openrewrite/.github/blob/main/CONTRIBUTING.md#contributing-fixes)?
I am unfortunately unable to do so.

