problem_statement:
JCase where guard is not present has invalid syntax after calling WithGuard
## What version of OpenRewrite are you using?
I am using `latest.release` of gradle plugin

## How are you running OpenRewrite?
gradle plugin to run the unit test/write recipe

## What is the smallest, simplest way to reproduce the problem?
Call `withGuard` on the second `JCase`
```java
class Test {
    void guardedCases(Object o) {
        switch (o) {
            case Integer i when i > 0 -> System.out.println("Perfect");
            case String s -> System.out.println("Great");
            default -> System.out.println("Ok");
        }
    }
}
```

## What did you expect to see?
```java
case String s when "YES".equalsIgnoreCase(s) -> System.out.println("Great");
```

## What did you see instead?
No space between the labels and the newly added guard
```java
case String swhen "YES".equalsIgnoreCase(s) -> System.out.println("Great");
```

## What is the full stack trace of any errors you encountered?
`getLabels` returns a `JContainer` of `JRightPadded` labels. When a guard is present, the last rightpadded contains a space/newline/... to print before the when. When the original case has no JRightPadded space (as the lambda has the space?) and we add a guard, the when is printed immediatly after. 
We could also change this in the Printer itself -> print " when" if the labels last expression had no/empty space.

## Are you interested in [contributing a fix to OpenRewrite](https://github.com/openrewrite/.github/blob/main/CONTRIBUTING.md#contributing-fixes)?
branch on the way

