problem_statement:
Idempotency issue with Java parser when no space between modifier and annotation: `private@Annotation`
## What version of OpenRewrite are you using?

Current main = 45ca3c98d074f7434f8d4aec781228619b21313d

## What is the smallest, simplest way to reproduce the problem?
```java
    @Test
    void modifierNoSpaceThenAnnotation() {
        rewriteRun(
          java(
            """
            public class Main {
              public@jdk.jfr.Name("A") static void main(String[] argv) {
               System.out.println("A");
              }
            }
            """
          )
        );
    }
```

## What did you expect to see?
no change

## What did you see instead?
```diff
- public@jdk.jfr.Name("A") static void main(String[] argv) {
+ @jdklic@jdk.jfr.Name("A") void main(String[] argv) {
```

## Context

Inspired by real-life: https://github.com/hivemq/hivemq-community-edition/blob/f13006a4206ebaba44379911b22c6ff571e7b746/src/main/java/com/hivemq/mqtt/services/PublishDistributorImpl.java#L210

