Sometimes the logs indicate a recipe stumbled over a particular pattern of code.
If you can share a code snippet that reproduces the issue, that will help us fix it faster.
We also accept [pull requests that merely replicate an issue](https://github.com/openrewrite/.github/blob/main/CONTRIBUTING.md#contributing-fixes), as a step up to a full fix.

A code snippet can be something simple like this, or similar for other languages:
-->
Run this test, it will failed:
- Outside the method definition, the `String out = QUX1` will be changed correctly
- **But within the method definition, the `String in = QUX1` will NOT changed**

```java
@Test
void shouldUpdateWithinMethod() {
    rewriteRun(
      spec -> spec.recipe(new ReplaceConstantWithAnotherConstant("foo.Bar.QUX1", "foo.Bar.QUX2")),
      java(
        """
          package foo;

          public class Bar {
              public static final String QUX1 = "QUX1";
              public static final String QUX2 = "QUX2";
          }
          """
      ),
      java(
        """
          import static foo.Bar.QUX1;

          class Test {
              String out = QUX1;
              void a() {
                  String in = QUX1;
              }
          }
          """,
        """
          import static foo.Bar.QUX2;

          class Test {
              String out = QUX2;
              void a() {
                  String in = QUX2;
              }
          }
          """
      )
    );
}
```

As for the reason, I did some troubleshooting and I thinks it's because of the redundant check `!isVariableDeclaration`:
https://github.com/openrewrite/rewrite/blob/main/rewrite-java/src/main/java/org/openrewrite/java/ReplaceConstantWithAnotherConstant.java#L82
https://github.com/openrewrite/rewrite/blob/main/rewrite-java/src/main/java/org/openrewrite/java/ReplaceConstantWithAnotherConstant.java#L129

I really cannot find any useful case for this `!isVariableDeclaration`, and even i remove it, all test cases can be passed. And actually if we are concern about duplicated definition (the same constant name), it won't causes any issue becuase it will be defensed by `isConstant`:
https://github.com/openrewrite/rewrite/blob/main/rewrite-java/src/main/java/org/openrewrite/java/ReplaceConstantWithAnotherConstant.java#L124

```java
@Test
void shouldUpdateWithinMethod3() {
    rewriteRun(
      spec -> spec.recipe(new ReplaceConstantWithAnotherConstant("foo.Bar.QUX1", "foo.Bar.QUX2")),
      java(
        """
          package foo;

          public class Bar {
              public static final String QUX1 = "QUX1";
              public static final String QUX2 = "QUX2";
          }
          """
      ),
      java(
        """
          import foo.Bar;

          import static foo.Bar.QUX2;

          class Test {
              public static final String QUX1 = "QUX111"; // the same name as Bar.QUX1

              void a() {
                  String in = Bar.QUX1;
                  String in2 = QUX2;
              }
          }
          """,
        """
          import foo.Bar;

          import static foo.Bar.QUX2;

          class Test {
              public static final String QUX1 = "QUX111"; // the same name as Bar.QUX1

              void a() {
                  String in = Bar.QUX2;
                  String in2 = QUX2;
              }
          }
          """
      )
    );
}
```

## What did you expect to see?
<!-- A code snippet, or a description of the behavior you expected helps us write a test to ensure the issue is fixed. -->
```java
import static foo.Bar.QUX2;

class Test {
    String out = QUX2;
    void a() {
        String in = QUX2;
    }
}
```

## What did you see instead?
<!-- A code snippet, or a description of the behavior you saw instead of the above expected result. -->
```java
import static foo.Bar.QUX1;
import static foo.Bar.QUX2;

class Test {
    String out = QUX2;
    void a() {
        String in = QUX1;
    }
}
```

