problem_statement:
Groovy parser does not correctly handle variables with nested type parameters.
When we attempt to parse:
```groovy
class A {
    def map = new HashMap<String, List<String>>()
}
```

What we actually get is:
```groovy
class A {
    def map = new HashMap<String, List<String>()>()
}
```

Reproduced in [VariableDeclarationsTest.nestedTypeParameters()](https://github.com/openrewrite/rewrite/blob/652654e57c5387c93c0c7d844b957c29ced52871/rewrite-groovy/src/test/java/org/openrewrite/groovy/tree/VariableDeclarationsTest.java#L188)

