```java
// this is an unknown import with invalid path
import java.util.GenClass1;
                  
public abstract class Foo {
      public abstract GenClass1 m(String a);
}
```

If use `RemoveUnusedImports` which uses `NoMissingTypes` as checker, it will wrongly remove the import.

But for below case, it will work for doing nothing.
```java
// this is an unknown import with invalid path
import java.util.GenClass1;
                  
public abstract class Foo {
      public abstract GenClass1 m();
}
```

The only difference is the first one has param (`String a`).

